               <interp inst="t17630413-17" type="year" value="1763"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17630413-17" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17630413"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17630413-17" type="date" value="17630413"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17630413-17-off93-c159" targOrder="Y" targets="t17630413-17-defend204 t17630413-17-off93 t17630413-17-verdict95"></join>
         
               <p>166. (M.) 
               <persName id="t17630413-17-defend204" type="defendantName">
                  Stair 
                  Burnett 
               <interp inst="t17630413-17-defend204" type="surname" value="Burnett"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630413-17-defend204" type="given" value="Stair"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630413-17-defend204" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was indicted for <rs id="t17630413-17-off93" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17630413-17-off93" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630413-17-off93" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing one pair of silver shoe-buckles, val. 12 s.
            </rs> the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17630413-17-victim206" type="victimName">
                     Philip 
                     Bellie 
                  <interp inst="t17630413-17-victim206" type="surname" value="Bellie"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630413-17-victim206" type="given" value="Philip"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630413-17-victim206" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17630413-17-off93 t17630413-17-victim206"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17630413-17-cd94" type="crimeDate">Feb. 23</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17630413-17-off93 t17630413-17-cd94"></join>. ++</p>
               <p>Philip Bellie. The prisoner had been 2 months in my service, I took him out of charity being almost naked; he went away, after which I missed my silver buckles. I taxed him with taking them, he owned he had, and that he had sold them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17630413-17-person207">
                  Benjamin 
                  Cartwright 
               <interp inst="t17630413-17-person207" type="surname" value="Cartwright"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630413-17-person207" type="given" value="Benjamin"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630413-17-person207" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a silversmith. I bought these buckles of the prisoner at the bar, (produced and deposed to by the prosecutor) they do not weigh two ounces, iron chapes and all, I gave him 8 s. for them.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>The night before I did this thing I was drunk. I brought down my master's shoes, and cleaned them, but where I put the buckles I do not know, or whether I put them in the shoes. I did not find them till three days after in my pocket, then I sold them.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17630413-17-verdict95" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17630413-17-verdict95" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>. <rs id="t17630413-17-punish96" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17630413-17-punish96" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17630413-17-defend204 t17630413-17-punish96"></join>
               T
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
